00:12:42.560 --> 00:12:45.700
when I was seven, eight years
old without understanding a word

00:12:45.700 --> 00:12:48.240
of what I was reading, but I read.

00:12:48.240 --> 00:12:53.770
So I think I became a writer
because of this diary.

00:12:53.770 --> 00:13:02.170
Because I had to tell people what
my mother and my father told me

00:13:02.170 --> 00:13:06.360
about what they had gone
through, and because I knew

00:13:06.360 --> 00:13:09.400
that my mother had a diary,
which I didn't understand,

00:13:09.400 --> 00:13:11.780
because I don't understand Serbian.

00:13:11.780 --> 00:13:17.270
And that someday, I would
want to write about it.

00:13:17.270 --> 00:13:25.950
So for me, writing is a
necessity, is a mission,

00:13:25.950 --> 00:13:32.220
and it's also very therapeutic
for me to overcome the fact

00:13:32.220 --> 00:13:35.860
that I'm the daughter of a survivor

00:13:35.860 --> 00:13:38.810
and all the things
that this fact implies.

00:13:38.810 --> 00:13:49.800
It implies a lot of guilt, a lot of
shame, and after writing this book,

00:13:49.800 --> 00:13:55.620
which was like the
